    "body": "Hey @Nikhilkumarravula, using `sudo` while installing Truffle can cause permissions errors and should be avoided. My advice would be to re-install Node and npm using a Node version manager like nvm. This is what npm recommends, you can check out [this npm article](https://docs.npmjs.com/resolving-eacces-permissions-errors-when-installing-packages-globally) about doing this. If you get a chance to try, then let us know how it goes!",
